<subSubSection id="C3106513E4638257FF493EDCFDEDFCE1" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BB53698E4638257FF493EDCFF25FDCE" blockId="10.[160,252,506,532]" box="[160,252,506,532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">
<heading id="D0FD81F4E4638257FF493EDCFF25FDCE" bold="true" box="[160,252,506,532]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF493EDCFF25FDCE" bold="true" box="[160,252,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Biology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB53698E4638257FF493D09FDEDFCE1" blockId="10.[160,1156,559,1208]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">
Adults and immatures of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FE303D09FDB5FD92" authorityName="Aléné &amp; Latar Vernyuy &amp; Djiéto-Lordon &amp; Burckhardt" authorityYear="2021" box="[473,620,559,584]" class="Insecta" family="Liviidae" genus="Diaphorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pfanderae">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FE303D09FDB5FD92" box="[473,620,559,584]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">D. pfanderae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were observed feeding on young plants of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FF493D74FE9BFDB1" box="[160,322,594,619]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Ozoroa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF493D74FE9BFDB1" box="[160,322,594,619]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">O. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially on the underside of leaves, along the petiole and the midrib, and even on fruit-bearing stalks. Eggs were laid on the leaf-blade near the central vein (
<figureCitation id="13312A1DE4638257FF413DB1FED0FD6A" box="[168,265,663,688]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,925,948]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,893]" captionTargetId="figure-239@7.[163,1153,142,893]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. Diaphorina pfanderae Aléné and Burckhardt sp. nov., egg and immatures. (a) Habitus of fifth instar, left side; (b) egg clusters and immatures; (c) caudal plate; (d) colony covered in honeydew; (e) circumanal ring." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5529948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5529948/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(b)). The different stages were always associated with the three ant species 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FF493D9CFD81FD09" authority="Emery, 1899" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1899" box="[160,600,698,723]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congolensis">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF493D9CFE61FD09" box="[160,440,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Camponotus congolensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B69E4638257FE2F3D9CFD81FD09" author="Emery C" box="[454,600,698,723]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" pagination="459 - 504" refId="ref6725" refString="Emery C. 1899. Fourmis d'Afrique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique. 43: 459 - 504." type="journal article" year="1899">Emery, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FD853D9CFB93FD09" authority="Mayr, 1862" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1862" box="[620,1098,698,723]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FD853D9CFC61FD09" box="[620,952,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Camponotus flavomarginatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B69E4638257FC2E3D9CFB93FD09" author="Mayr G" box="[967,1098,698,723]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" pagination="649 - 776" refId="ref7206" refString="Mayr G. 1862. Myrmecologische Studien. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien. 12: 649 - 776." type="journal article" year="1862">Mayr, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FF493DFAFEB4FD2F" box="[160,365,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF493DFAFE99FD2F" box="[160,320,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Crematogaster</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FE973DFAFDC5FD2F" box="[382,540,732,757]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FDC23DFAFD75FD2F" box="[555,684,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Formicidae</taxonomicName>
). Of these, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FCDE3DFAFC0FFD2F" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1899" box="[823,982,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congolensis">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FCDE3DFAFC0FFD2F" box="[823,982,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">C. congolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the most abundant, with 391 individuals, followed by 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FD5C3DD9FC5BFCC2" box="[693,898,767,792]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FD5C3DD9FC8CFCC2" box="[693,853,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Crematogaster</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(288 individuals) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FF493C04FEB7FCE1" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1862" box="[160,366,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF493C04FEB7FCE1" box="[160,366,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">C. flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(220 individuals).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3106513E4638257FF293C62FBF6FB62" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB53698E4638257FF293C62FD01FB8A" blockId="10.[160,1156,559,1208]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">
The infestation of leaves by the psyllids did not significantly differ between the three age classes of leaves (Χ2 = 1.78; p = 0.41) (
<tableCitation id="C6880323E4638257FD873C41FD66FC5A" box="[622,703,871,896]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="11.[160,216,142,165]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Table 1. Distribution of Diaphorina pfanderae Aléné and Burckhardt sp. nov. and its associated ant species on old leaves (O), young leaves (Y) and very young leaves (VY) of Ozoroa pulcherrima. Numbers represent insect abundance (absolute and relative values)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF756610E4628256FF493FA8FD3AFF3A" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" tableUuid="DF756610E4628256FF493FA8FD3AFF3A">Table 1</tableCitation>
), and the relative numbers of psyllids on young and very young leaves were approximately the same (37.24% and 38.86%, respectively). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FF1D3C8AFDD1FC1F" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1899" box="[244,520,940,965]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congolensis">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF1D3C8AFDD1FC1F" box="[244,520,940,965]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Camponotus congolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was predominantly found associated with colonies of immature psyllids on the very young leaves (47.57%), while 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FCAA3CE9FBC8FC32" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1862" box="[835,1041,975,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FCAA3CE9FBC8FC32" box="[835,1041,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">C. flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was most abundant on young leaves (41.82%). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FDD03CD4FCD9FBD1" box="[569,768,1010,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FDD03CD4FD00FBD1" box="[569,729,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Crematogaster</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, in contrast, was evenly distributed among the three age classes of leaves (
<tableCitation id="C6880323E4638257FDB53B32FD77FBF7" box="[604,686,1044,1069]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="11.[160,216,142,165]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Table 1. Distribution of Diaphorina pfanderae Aléné and Burckhardt sp. nov. and its associated ant species on old leaves (O), young leaves (Y) and very young leaves (VY) of Ozoroa pulcherrima. Numbers represent insect abundance (absolute and relative values)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF756610E4628256FF493FA8FD3AFF3A" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" tableUuid="DF756610E4628256FF493FA8FD3AFF3A">Table 1</tableCitation>
). These ants would often, but not always, build shelters around the colonies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FDAC3B11FD0BFB8A" authorityName="Aléné &amp; Latar Vernyuy &amp; Djiéto-Lordon &amp; Burckhardt" authorityYear="2021" box="[581,722,1079,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Liviidae" genus="Diaphorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pfanderae">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FDAC3B11FD0BFB8A" box="[581,722,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">D. pfanderae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB53698E4638257FF293B7CFBF6FB62" blockId="10.[160,1156,559,1208]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">
The Spearman’s test performed between ant species and the psyllid showed that the number of individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FE5E3B5AFD9BFB4F" authorityName="Aléné &amp; Latar Vernyuy &amp; Djiéto-Lordon &amp; Burckhardt" authorityYear="2021" box="[439,578,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Liviidae" genus="Diaphorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pfanderae">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FE5E3B5AFD9BFB4F" box="[439,578,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">D. pfanderae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was positively and significantly correlated with that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FF573BB9FE81FB62" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1899" box="[190,344,1183,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congolensis">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FF573BB9FE81FB62" box="[190,344,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">C. congolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED1BAE5DE4638257FE8C3BB9FEACFB62" box="[357,373,1183,1208]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">R</collectionCode>
= 0.49, P &lt;0.001) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D1BE4638257FD933BB9FC98FB62" box="[634,833,1183,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B97EEA8AE4638257FD933BB9FCC3FB62" box="[634,794,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">Crematogaster</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED1BAE5DE4638257FCA73BB9FC87FB62" box="[846,862,1183,1208]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="10" pageNumber="1659">R</collectionCode>
= 0.50, P &lt;0.001).
</paragraph>
